Commands




mkdocs new [dir-name]
 - Create a new project.


mkdocs serve
 - Start the live-reloading docs server.


mkdocs build
 - Build the documentation site.


mkdocs help
 - Print this help message.

 - This is a test

docs.text:
Chlorine (Hypochlorite Feed System)


Strength of bleach
   




What is chlorine?


Chlorine is a chemical used in our treatment process. Chlorine is a disinfectent--which means it inactivates pathogens 
(many of them, but not all of them)
. Although it can be purchased in several different forms, we purchase it in the form of sodium hypochlorite (NaClO).




Strength 


We purchase sodium hypochlorite that is approximately 12.5% active (by weight). It can also be expressed as 15% active (by volume). This means that 1 pound of sodium hypochlorite solution will have about 0.125 lbs of active chlorine. Likewise, 1 gallon of sodium hypochlorite of bleach will consist of 0.15 active gallons.   






Note


You should note that the title will be automatically capitalized.
